==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relegate
<hw>Rel"e*gate</hw> <pr>(r?l"?-g?t)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Relegated</conjf>
<pr>(-g?`t?d)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Relegating</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L. <ets>relegatus</ets>, p.
p. of <ets>relegare</ets>; pref. <ets>re-</ets> re- + <ets>legare</ets>
to send with a commission or charge. See <er>Legate</er>.]</ety> <def>To
remove, usually to an inferior position; to consign; to transfer;
specifically, to send into exile; to banish.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>It [the Latin language] was <qex>relegated</qex> into the study of
the scholar.</q> <rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relegation</ent>⟦br⟧
